<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910211-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>910211-0026.</DOCID><HL>   International:   `Environmental Audits'   Being Considered by EC</HL><DATE>02/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9</SO><CO>   EUROP</CO><IN>ENVIRONMENT (ENV)</IN><LP>   BRUSSELS -- The European Community Commission isconsidering establishing a system to monitor companies'environmental performance.   An EC spokesman said the commission is consultingcompanies and other interested parties before proposing draftlegislation. The commission hasn't decided whetherenvironmental audits by companies should be mandatory orvoluntary, he said.</LP><TEXT>   The system would seek to make available to publicauthorities such environmental information as energyconservation, pollution control and transportation of wastein a range of industries. Companies would be asked to carryout annual audits and publish statements on the results.   Environmental activists are expected to push for amandatory system, but this would be resisted as too costly bymany concerns.   EC officials said that even a voluntary scheme would putpressure on companies to pay more attention to theirenvironmental performance.</TEXT></DOC>